  "text": "The first \"≤\" uses the Taylor series development of ln and the second one is a geometric sum. This calculation also shows that the overall number of elements in any subcube in any level of recursion is balanced. We argue that the initial random data distribution also implies a random data distribution of the elements in each subcube. Therefore, the overall balance of the number of elements also implies that the individual number of elements in each PE is not too imbalanced. [CITATION_1] Finally, random data shuffling also helps our simple local tie-breaking -each PE has a random sample of the globally available data and hence our local balancing approximates a global balancing.",
